<subSubSection id="C3486561E935C730FF7CCF4C36C0FB45" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BED36EAE935C730FF7CCF4C36C0FB45" blockId="3.[136,1452,1129,1516]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="B926EAF8E935C730FF7CCF4C350CFB0B" bold="true" box="[136,261,1129,1155]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D69E935C730FED5CF4F3718FB0C" authorityName="Garcia-Beltran" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Garcia-Beltran" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[289,785,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pinnatum" subSpecies="oblongifolium">
<emphasis id="B926EAF8E935C730FED5CF4F3613FB0C" box="[289,538,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">Cenostigma pinnatum</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B926EAF8E935C730FD80CF4F3718FB0C" box="[628,785,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">oblongifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from the typical subspecies by its leaves with mostly five or more leaflet pairs (vs. mostly up to five leaflet pairs), cordate or cordate-truncate at base (vs. oblique), and ciliate on the margin (vs. non-ciliate).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3486561E935C730FF49CFF3377AFA64" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED36EAE935C730FF49CFF3377AFA64" blockId="3.[136,1452,1129,1516]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="B926EAF8E935C730FF49CFF335AAFB78" bold="true" box="[189,419,1238,1264]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">
Notes on 
<typeStatus id="54E98848E935C730FEDACFF33597FB78" box="[302,414,1238,1264]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">lectotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
—In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D69E935C730FD5ECFF337F7FB78" authority="Urb." authorityName="Urban" authorityYear="1900" box="[682,1022,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Caesalpinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oblongifolia">
<emphasis id="B926EAF8E935C730FD5ECFF337CAFB78" box="[682,963,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">Caesalpinia oblongifolia</emphasis>
Urb.
</taxonomicName>
a 
<typeStatus id="54E98848E935C730FBEECFF33075FB78" box="[1050,1148,1238,1264]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">holotype</typeStatus>
was not indicated, since it refers to part of the 
<emphasis id="B926EAF8E935C730FE90CFDF3619FA9C" box="[356,528,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">C. Wright 2360</emphasis>
collection, but not a single specimen, since a particular herbarium is not specified. Therefore, all the duplicates of 
<emphasis id="B926EAF8E935C730FE1FCE3B3691FAB0" box="[491,664,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">C. Wright 2360</emphasis>
corresponding to this entity (without considering those that under the same C. Wright number belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D69E935C730FDEDCE6737DCFAD4" authority="subsp. pinnatum" box="[537,981,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cenostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pinnatum" subSpecies="pinnatum">
<emphasis id="B926EAF8E935C730FDEDCE67371BFAD4" box="[537,786,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">Cenostigma pinnatum</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B926EAF8E935C730FC9FCE6637DCFAD4" box="[875,981,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">pinnatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the herbaria in which they are found are considered 
<typeStatus id="54E98848E935C730FEC0CE43359FFA08" box="[308,406,1382,1408]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">syntypes</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC34B1BE935C730FE52CE43368FFA08" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[422,646,1382,1408]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" refId="ref4755" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code). Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">Turland &amp; al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
: Article 40 Note 1). These elements were not considered by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC34B1BE935C730FACDCE433514FA2C" author="Barreto, A. &amp; Beyra, A." pageId="3" pageNumber="294" pagination="179 - 185" refId="ref4128" refString="Barreto, A. &amp; Beyra, A. (1998) Acerca de Caesalpinia pinnata (Griseb.) C. Wr. (Fabaceae, Caesalpinioideae) y especies afines. Fontqueria 48: 179 - 185." type="journal article" year="1998">Barreto &amp; Beyra (1998)</bibRefCitation>
when designating the material deposited in HAC as a 
<typeStatus id="54E98848E935C730FC71CEAF37E6FA2C" box="[901,1007,1418,1444]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">lectotype</typeStatus>
, who carried out this nomenclatural act due to the destruction of the existing one in B considered as a 
<typeStatus id="54E98848E935C730FCAACE8B37CDFA40" box="[862,964,1454,1480]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">holotype</typeStatus>
. However, regardless of the reason for the lectotypification carried out by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC34B1BE935C730FE1DCEF736FEFA64" author="Barreto, A. &amp; Beyra, A." box="[489,759,1490,1516]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" pagination="179 - 185" refId="ref4128" refString="Barreto, A. &amp; Beyra, A. (1998) Acerca de Caesalpinia pinnata (Griseb.) C. Wr. (Fabaceae, Caesalpinioideae) y especies afines. Fontqueria 48: 179 - 185." type="journal article" year="1998">Barreto &amp; Beyra (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, it is valid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
